President Joe Biden has declared a state of emergency in Massachusetts due to the effects of Hurricane Lee from September 15 to September 17, 2023. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to alleviate the hardship caused by the emergency. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and equipment to help mitigate the impacts of the emergency. Specifically, FEMA will provide 75 percent federal funding for emergency protective measures, including mass care such as evacuation and sheltering support. E. Craig Levy, Sr. of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. For further information, media can contact the FEMA news desk.